The paper deals with the efficient enumeration of top-k answers for conjunctive queries against relational databases, which is a problem that falls under the scope of database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of ranking functions and priority queues also suggests a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the discussion of lower bounds and optimality conjectures indicates a possible link to computational complexity (cs.CC).
